## Context

Sixteenth run — web search available. 10 projects active (ts-convergent-polypharmacology added since last run). Created 3 journal entries (#2279, #2280, #2281) and 2 tasks (#1398, #1400). No assigned tasks to process.

### Key findings recorded:
- **ts-rare-variant-convergence (journal #2279, task #1398):** Saia et al. clinical exome study NOW PUBLISHED in Frontiers in Psychiatry 2026 (doi:10.3389/fpsyt.2026.1744145). 80 TS children, 13.7% with potentially causative variants. 8 new candidate genes: PNKD, SLC6A1, CACNA1D, BRPF1, KMT2C, SMARCA2, PTEN, RERE. Chromatin remodeling cluster (BRPF1/KMT2C/SMARCA2) may be new convergent pathway. Dual genetic model: rare variants → severe/syndromic, polygenic → milder familial.
- **ts-convergent-polypharmacology (journal #2280, task #1400):** WWC1/KIBRA paper (Science Advances 2025, doi:10.1126/sciadv.adr4588, PMC11952098). W88C mutation → KIBRA degradation → Hippo pathway activation → dopamine dysregulation. D2 antagonists reduce motor tics, D1 antagonists restore sensorimotor gating. Combination D1+D2 more effective than single-agent. Validates polypharmacology hypothesis.
- **Monitoring (journal #2281):** Comprehensive status update. Kraft v2 on bioRxiv but GEO still unavailable.

